<TITLE> Khaleda heads for Barisal rally </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 12 (bdnews24.com)  Opposition chief Khaleda Zia left Dhaka for Barisal to attend a divisional rally on Wednesday. She will address the rally to be held at the district city's Bells Park ground at around 3pm. The convoy of the BNP chief left her cantonment house at around 9am. Party's standing committee member Sarwari Rahman is accompanying her, Khaleda's press secretary Maruf Kamal Khan said. This will be her first speech in the city since the Dec 29, 2008 national elections. Standing committee member Mirza Abbas, who has already arrived in Barisal, told bdnews24.com that all preparations were complete. This is the fourth of six 'grand rallies' planned across the country. The first rally was held in Chittagong on Mar 29, the second one in Khulna on Apr 18 and the third in Rajshhai on May 5. BNP will hold the next meeting in Dhaka on May 19. The last meeting will be held in Sylhet. 
